  "description_snippet": "**VULNERABILITY DETAILS**   \nIn ~WebContentsImpl, if mouse_lock_widget_ is non-nullptr, it then calls the member function RejectMouseLockOrUnlockIfNecessary [1]. The mouse_lock_widget_ will not be assigned to nullptr if there is an ongoing lock mouse request and WebContentsImpl::GotResponseToLock"
